Homeland is an American psychological thriller television series developed by Howard Gordon and Alex Gansa, based on the Israeli series "Prisoners of War" created by Gideon Raff. The series stars Claire Danes as Carrie Mathison, a CIA operations officer who has come to believe that an American prisoner was turned by the enemy, and now poses a significant risk to national security. It premiered in the United States on Showtime on October 2, 2011.
, 24 episodes of "Homeland" have aired.
Episode list.
Season 3 (2013).
On October 22, 2012, "Homeland" was renewed for a third season, which will consist of 12 episodes. Production for the third season is expected to begin in late May 2013, and will premiere on September 29, 2013.
